description:
### Expected behavior
Would expect to be able to control certain config settings such as:

- karma's browser timeouts
- folders which istanbul-instrument-loader looks at or
- folders which istanbul gives coverage for

### Actual behavior

- cannot do any of this.  At one point we could, but it seems files at the root level of the SPA are now
being ignored.

### Steps to reproduce
- try to extend an config.  An example of what we tried is this:
```
function getConfig(config) {

  require('../node_modules/@blackbaud/skyux-builder/config/karma/shared.karma.conf')(config);
  config..set({
    client: {
      captureConsole: false
    },
    browserDisconnectTimeout: 25000,
    browserNoActivityTimeout: 25000
  });
}

module.exports = getConfig;
```

One of the reasons we have to use skyux advanced mode is we have to override a function from an external library in order to bootstrap correctly.

Here is our bootstrapping code in main.ts

`Office.initialize = function () {
  platformBrowserDynamic().bootstrapModule(AppModule);
}`

In order for our project to use easy mode we will need a way to configure this.

An example on how you could use a third-party component/service...

```
import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { DragulaService, DragulaModule } from 'ng2-dragula/ng2-dragula';

// Specify entry components, module-level providers, etc. here.
@NgModule({
  imports: [
    DragulaModule
  ],
  exports: [
    DragulaModule
  ],
  providers: [
    DragulaService
  ],
  entryComponents: []
})
export class AppExtrasModule { }
```

From https://github.com/blackbaud/skyux-cli/issues/99

Browser original width:
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/11943543/17625991/dd47ffcc-6070-11e6-9c67-c3e35726e802.png)

Browser made smaller:  note one tile has disappeared
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/11943543/17626016/07c34482-6071-11e6-86db-203952c84d4a.png)

Browser back to original size: both tiles end up in right column
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/11943543/17626030/1eefc09a-6071-11e6-8851-e5e49352eda4.png)

We have provided both single and multicolumn layouts in the config:

```
layout: {
  singleColumn: {
    tiles: [
      { id: 'moon-grant-summary-tile', isCollapsed: false },
      { id: 'moon-grant-summary-tile', isCollapsed: false }
    ]
  },
  multiColumn: [
    {
      tiles: [
        { id: 'moon-grant-summary-tile', isCollapsed: false }
      ]
    },
    {
      tiles: [
        { id: 'moon-grant-summary-tile', isCollapsed: false }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
